@startuml UPVEST_Architecture
' System architecture overview for UPVEST platform

actor User as U

package "Frontend (Browser)" {
  [Web UI] as WebUI
}

package "Backend Services" {
  [API Server\n(backend_api.py)] as API
  [Auth Manager\n(auth_manager.py)] as Auth
  [Database Manager\n(database_manager.py)] as DB
  [Trading Engine\n(trading_execution.py)] as TE
  [Strategy Engine\n(strategy_engine.py)] as SE
  [AI Decision Engine\n(ai_agent/ai_decision_engine.py)] as AI
  [Risk Manager\n(risk_manager.py)] as RM
  [Trading Mode Manager\n(trading_mode_manager.py)] as TM
  [Market Data Fetcher\n(market_data_fetcher.py)] as MD
  [Upstox Connector\n(upstox.py)] as Broker
}

U --> WebUI : interacts via browser
WebUI --> API : REST calls (status, portfolio, bot control, predictions)
API --> Auth : validate / create user
API --> DB : read/write trades, summaries, user data
API --> TE : start/stop bot, query status
API --> AI : /api/ai/predict endpoint

TE --> SE : generate strategy signals
TE --> AI : request price prediction / decision
TE --> RM : check risk constraints
TE --> TM : determine paper/live mode
TE --> Broker : place orders / fetch positions
MD --> DB : populate historical data
Broker --> DB : update balances/positions
DB --> WebUI : serve portfolio & history

note right of API
Backend is Python FastAPI
handles CORS for frontend
and orchestrates modules
end note

@enduml